<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/6157</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-19">September 19, 1939</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The British Ambassador called at his own request and handed me an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>,<note n="52" xml:id="d652fn52">
                                <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> a copy of which is attached, in
                            regard to the Mexican oil situation. I thanked him for this information
                            concerning the attitude of his Government toward the matter and added
                            that my Government was doing all it possibly could to aid in bringing
                            about a satisfactory settlement of the oil question.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>